00:03:29.420 --> 00:03:31.420
That's because today marks the 15th wedding anniversary

00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:33.420
of our neighbors, the Supersteens.

00:03:33.420 --> 00:03:36.420
That means for the fourth year in a row,

00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:40.300
Mr. and Mrs. O'Pristine will ask me to babysit for them.

00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:43.020
Any other time of the year, I can find a way to get out of it.

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:45.820
But somehow, on their anniversary, no matter what I do,

00:03:45.820 --> 00:03:47.700
I get guilt-tripped into the job.

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:49.300
So what's so bad about that?

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:53.620
Historically, babysitting has always been one tough business.

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:56.140
Even in prehistoric times, the little Neanderthals

00:03:56.140 --> 00:04:00.820
couldn't be trusted.

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:02.220
But with the grown-ups gone, it

00:04:02.220 --> 00:04:05.380
didn't take them two minutes to start wrecking the place.

00:04:05.380 --> 00:04:07.740
Talk about primitive.

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:11.420
As time passed, things went from bad to worse.

00:04:11.420 --> 00:04:14.620
Medieval parents were just as clueless.

00:04:14.620 --> 00:04:16.620
And for the babysitter, the castle

00:04:16.620 --> 00:04:18.700
became a chamber of horrors.

00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:22.380
Being locked in the dungeon would have been a relief.

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:24.940
Today, babysitters are paid in cold hard cash,

00:04:24.940 --> 00:04:28.500
watch tons of TV, and talk on the phone all night long.

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:30.420
But no perks are worth babysitting little Elsie

00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:32.940
Soapristine for the fourth year in a row.

00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:35.140
If I wind up minding that brat again,

00:04:35.140 --> 00:04:36.300
it's going to be different.

00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:37.740
It's going to get ugly.

00:04:37.740 --> 00:05:31.500
This year, it's going to be war.

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:34.900
